TITLE: Extending JWT Session with User ID in Auth.js (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to add the user's ID to the JWT token and session object using the jwt and session callbacks in Auth.js configuration. It allows access to the user's ID in subsequent API calls and through auth() or useSession() functions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextauthjs/next-auth/blob/main/docs/pages/guides/extending-the-session.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
callbacks: {
  jwt({ token, user }) {
    if (user) { // User is available during sign-in
      token.id = user.id
    }
    return token
  },
  session({ session, token }) {
    session.user.id = token.id
    return session
  },
},
```

