TITLE: Error Handling for Token Refresh in Server Component
DESCRIPTION: This server component demonstrates how to handle refresh token errors by forcing re-authentication when a token refresh fails. It uses the auth() function to check the session state and redirects to sign in if needed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextauthjs/next-auth/blob/main/docs/pages/guides/refresh-token-rotation.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { auth, signIn } from "@/auth"

export default async function Page() {
  const session = await auth()
  if (session?.error === "RefreshTokenError") {
    await signIn("google") // Force sign in to obtain a new set of access and refresh tokens
  }
}
```

