TITLE: Extending Session Type in Next.js Auth Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to extend the default Session interface in Next.js using TypeScript module augmentation to add custom properties like user address while preserving default session properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextauthjs/next-auth/blob/main/docs/pages/getting-started/typescript.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import NextAuth, { type DefaultSession } from "next-auth"

declare module "next-auth" {
  interface Session {
    user: {
      /** The user's postal address. */
      address: string
    } & DefaultSession["user"]
  }
}

export const { auth, handlers } = NextAuth({
  callbacks: {
    session({ session, token, user }) {
      return {
        ...session,
        user: {
          ...session.user,
          address: user.address,
        },
      }
    },
  },
})
```

