TITLE: Using Role for Authorization in Next.js
DESCRIPTION: This Next.js server component demonstrates how to use the user's role for authorization. It checks if the user has an 'admin' role before rendering protected content.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextauthjs/next-auth/blob/main/docs/pages/guides/role-based-access-control.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { auth } from "@/auth";

export default async function Page() {
  const session = await auth();

  if (session?.user?.role === "admin") {
    return <p>You are an admin, welcome!</p>;
  }

  return <p>You are not authorized to view this page!</p>;
}
```

