TITLE: Extending NextAuth Session Type in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet demonstrates how to extend the NextAuth session interface to include the supabaseAccessToken and additional user properties. It's defined in a separate type declaration file.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextauthjs/next-auth/blob/main/docs/pages/getting-started/adapters/supabase.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import NextAuth, { type DefaultSession } from "next-auth"

declare module "next-auth" {
  // Returned by `useSession`, `getSession` and received as a prop on the `SessionProvider` React Context
  interface Session {
    // A JWT which can be used as Authorization header with supabase-js for RLS.
    supabaseAccessToken?: string
    user: {
      // The user's postal address
      address: string
    } & DefaultSession["user"]
  }
}
```

