TITLE: Running D1 Migrations
DESCRIPTION: Example of how to run D1 migrations to create necessary tables. It uses the 'up' function from the D1 adapter to create tables if they don't exist.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextauthjs/next-auth/blob/main/docs/pages/getting-started/adapters/d1.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { up } from "@auth/d1-adapter"

let migrated = false
async function migrationHandle({ event, resolve }) {
  if (!migrated) {
    try {
      await up(event.platform.env.db)
      migrated = true
    } catch (e) {
      console.log(e.cause.message, e.message)
    }
  }
  return resolve(event)
}
```

