TITLE: Extending Session Type in Qwik Auth Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates session interface extension for Qwik framework using TypeScript module augmentation to add custom user properties while maintaining default functionality.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextauthjs/next-auth/blob/main/docs/pages/getting-started/typescript.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { DefaultSession, QwikAuth$ } from "@auth/qwik"

declare module "@auth/qwik" {
  interface Session {
    user: {
      /** The user's postal address. */
      address: string
    } & DefaultSession["user"]
  }
}

export const { onRequest, useSession, useSignIn, useSignOut } = QwikAuth$(
  () => ({
    callbacks: {
      session({ session, token, user }) {
        return {
          ...session,
          user: {
            ...session.user,
            address: user.address,
          },
        }
      },
    },
  })
)
```

