TITLE: Configuring Neon Adapter with Express
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of the Neon adapter with Auth.js in an Express application. Sets up authentication routes and connects to the Neon database.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextauthjs/next-auth/blob/main/docs/pages/getting-started/adapters/neon.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
import { ExpressAuth } from "@auth/express"
import NeonAdapter from "@auth/neon-adapter"
import { Pool } from "@neondatabase/serverless"

const pool = new Pool({ connectionString: process.env.DATABASE_URL })

const app = express()

app.set("trust proxy", true)
app.use(
  "/auth/*",
  ExpressAuth({
    providers: [],
    adapter: NeonAdapter(pool),
  })
)
```

